@startuml
title VR Scene Exploration Application - Data Flow Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "React Client\n(App.js)" as Client
participant "React Router" as Router
participant "A-Frame\nVR Renderer" as VR
participant "Express Server\n(server.js)" as Server
participant "Utilities\n(utilities.js)" as Utils
participant "Controllers" as Controller
participant "Sequelize ORM" as Sequelize
participant "MariaDB" as DB
participant "AWS S3" as S3

== User Authentication ==
User -> Client: Access application
Client -> Router: Navigate to auth page
Router -> Client: Render auth component
User -> Client: Submit signup/signin (email, password)
Client -> Server: POST /api/auth/signup or /api/auth/signin
Server -> Controller: Validate credentials
Controller -> Sequelize: Query user data
Sequelize -> DB: SELECT from users table
DB --> Sequelize: Return user data
Sequelize --> Controller: User record
Controller --> Server: Authentication result
Server --> Client: Auth token/session
Client -> Client: Update authentication state
Client -> Router: Redirect to lobby

== VR Scene Exploration ==
User -> Client: Select scene from lobby
Client -> Router: Navigate to scene route
Router -> Client: Render scene component
Client -> Server: GET /api/photos/scene
Server -> Controller: Fetch scene photos
Controller -> Sequelize: Query photos
Sequelize -> DB: SELECT from photos table
DB --> Sequelize: Photo records
Sequelize --> Controller: Photo list with S3 URLs
Controller --> Server: Photo data
Server --> Client: Scene photo metadata
Client -> S3: Fetch 360° images
S3 --> Client: Image data
Client -> VR: Initialize A-Frame scene
VR -> VR: Render 360° environment
VR --> User: Display VR scene

== Image Upload ==
User -> Client: Upload 360° image
Client -> Client: Encode image to base64
Client -> Server: POST /api/photos/upload (base64 data)
Server -> Utils: Decode base64 image
Utils --> Server: Binary image data
Server -> S3: Upload image to bucket
S3 --> Server: S3 URL
Server -> Controller: Save photo metadata
Controller -> Sequelize: INSERT photo record
Sequelize -> DB: INSERT into photos table
DB --> Sequelize: Confirmation
Sequelize --> Controller: Photo record created
Controller --> Server: Photo metadata
Server --> Client: Upload success + photo data
Client -> Client: Update state with new photo
Client --> User: Display upload confirmation

== Bookmark Management ==
User -> Client: Bookmark Wikipedia article
Client -> Server: POST /api/bookmarks (article URL)
Server -> Utils: Fetch Wikipedia article
Utils -> Utils: Parse article content
Utils --> Server: Article data
Server -> Controller: Save bookmark
Controller -> Sequelize: INSERT bookmark
Sequelize -> DB: INSERT into bookmarks table
DB --> Sequelize: Confirmation
Sequelize --> Controller: Bookmark created
Controller --> Server: Bookmark data
Server --> Client: Success response
Client -> Client: Update bookmark state
Client --> User: Display bookmark confirmation

== Social Interaction - Comments ==
User -> Client: Submit comment (text/voice)
Client -> Server: POST /api/comments (photo_id, comment_text)
Server -> Controller: Create comment
Controller -> Sequelize: INSERT comment
Sequelize -> DB: INSERT into comments table
DB --> Sequelize: Confirmation
Sequelize --> Controller: Comment record
Controller --> Server: Comment data
Server --> Client: Comment created
Client -> Client: Update comments list
Client --> User: Display new comment

== Social Interaction - Likes ==
User -> Client: Like photo
Client -> Server: POST /api/likes (photo_id)
Server -> Controller: Create like
Controller -> Sequelize: INSERT like
Sequelize -> DB: INSERT into likes table
DB --> Sequelize: Confirmation
Sequelize --> Controller: Like record
Controller --> Server: Like count updated
Server --> Client: Updated like count
Client -> Client: Update UI with new like count
Client --> User: Display updated like count

== User Profile ==
User -> Client: View profile
Client -> Server: GET /api/users/profile
Server -> Controller: Fetch user data
Controller -> Sequelize: Query user with relations
Sequelize -> DB: SELECT user, photos, bookmarks
DB --> Sequelize: User data with relations
Sequelize --> Controller: Complete user profile
Controller --> Server: Profile data
Server --> Client: User profile information
Client -> S3: Fetch profile picture
S3 --> Client: Profile image
Client --> User: Display profile

@enduml
